WEBVTT

00:06.621 --> 00:09.761
Ramen.
Let's send Takeda too.

00:09.861 --> 00:15.301
Shall we?
Hello?

00:16.281 --> 00:17.281
Yeah, hello?
Takeda?

00:18.322 --> 00:19.402
Ah, yeah.
It's Minamikawa.

00:20.082 --> 00:23.482
Takeda, know ramen?
Yeah, I eat it.

00:23.482 --> 00:27.062
Sorry, you got a minute?
Ah, yeah, I do.

00:27.462 --> 00:30.103
So look up Karamenya...
Okay.

00:30.603 --> 00:33.583
Masumoto. The "masu" is the same kanji as
in Masuzoe.

00:34.203 --> 00:39.603
The question is what words are written on
the bottom of the bowl for their Original Spicy Noodles.

00:40.423 --> 00:43.944
Can you go eat there now and check for us?
Huh...?

00:43.964 --> 00:47.264
Uh... okay.
We'll call you back in an hour or two.

00:47.924 --> 00:50.404
Please.
Yeah, Karamenya Masumoto.

00:50.424 --> 00:53.884
Sorry.
Man, this would suck. What a pain.

00:54.225 --> 00:58.405
Think we can do the 48 positions?
No way.

00:58.405 --> 00:59.865
Eighteen.
We'd use ten right away, wouldn't we?

00:59.865 --> 01:01.205
Yeah, we'd burn ten easy.
For sure.

01:01.745 --> 01:04.345
Even if they just read one and we answer,
and read one and we answer...

01:05.657 --> 01:07.514
we'd still use like thirteen.
Yeah, easy.

01:08.186 --> 01:11.526
The 48 positions are scary.
Kashu-san.

01:11.986 --> 01:15.106
Kashu-san, it's Shinichi.
Shinichi Omokuri Geinin.

01:15.590 --> 01:16.662
Yeah, yeah, Shinichi... yeah.

01:16.662 --> 01:18.327
So, Shinichi, we're kinda locked up right
now...

01:18.327 --> 01:20.907
We need you to look up an answer for us,
right now.

01:20.907 --> 01:22.621
Calm down, calm down.
Pant, pant... okay, okay.

01:22.647 --> 01:28.327
Right, so you know the 48 sex positions?
The 48 sex positions?

01:28.327 --> 01:29.847
Yeah, the 48 positions. The naughty ones.

01:30.628 --> 01:32.928
I'll call back in ten minutes, so can you
have the answer ready?

01:33.168 --> 01:35.328
You can just check on your phone.
That's a good junior.

01:35.388 --> 01:36.928
Ah, got it.
Sorry, thanks.

01:37.228 --> 01:39.528
Everyone's so nice.
They accept it so fast.

01:41.868 --> 01:43.769
Like they just go look it up right away.
Yeah.

01:45.529 --> 01:46.569
Nothing on the inside.
Yeah.

01:46.569 --> 01:47.549
Damn.
Nope.

01:47.549 --> 01:51.949
This spot looks suspicious too.
They made it really well.

01:52.129 --> 01:57.710
Could it be hidden somewhere like this?
Like inside that thing?

01:57.710 --> 02:02.370
Man, finding the key in all this is
brutal. Yeah.

02:02.390 --> 02:05.630
Jeez.
Jeez.

02:06.571 --> 02:08.751
What is this?
Isn't it that thing?

02:10.031 --> 02:12.731
Isn't this a fortune cookie?
This?

02:13.251 --> 02:15.611
It's a fortune cookie.
There's something inside...

02:15.691 --> 02:17.511
Oh, there is!
No way, no way.

02:17.711 --> 02:19.032
Something came out.
No way.

02:19.032 --> 02:22.472
Oh, it's a fortune.
Wait, it says something good.

02:22.892 --> 02:24.712
Yeah.
This probably has some kind of hint on it.

02:24.712 --> 02:27.392
The writing... yeah.
Okay, got it.

02:27.552 --> 02:29.852
What does it say?
Sandals.

02:30.873 --> 02:32.073
Oh!
Sandals.

02:33.993 --> 02:35.493
Oh!
Something came!

02:35.673 --> 02:38.133
Oh!
What, what, what?

02:38.693 --> 02:39.693
No way!
Huh?

02:40.073 --> 02:42.154
Something came!
Hey!

02:42.224 --> 02:43.224
What?
Somebody came!

02:43.534 --> 02:45.594
Hey!
This is nuts. This isn't normal.

02:45.714 --> 02:47.994
It said sandals, and sandals showed up.
Huh?

02:48.374 --> 02:50.554
Huh?
That's insane.

02:50.874 --> 02:56.355
We don't even have shoes right now, so...
maybe that means...

02:57.135 --> 02:58.975
it's for getting ready to go outside?
Ah.

02:58.975 --> 03:00.675
Oh, that's what it means.
Yeah.

03:01.235 --> 03:05.055
No way.
So if we eat them one by one,

03:05.142 --> 03:06.356
huh?
stuff to help us get outside comes out?

03:06.356 --> 03:09.116
So then...
do I get to keep the sandals?

03:10.256 --> 03:11.816
No, there've gotta be more, obviously.

03:11.976 --> 03:14.976
Then what do we do? We need rules,
or we'll fight later.

03:15.876 --> 03:18.037
Maybe whatever you eat belongs to you.

03:18.793 --> 03:21.221
Okay, then whatever you pull out is yours.
Whatever you pull is yours.

03:21.221 --> 03:22.221
Okay.
Okay!

03:22.777 --> 03:25.517
Got the sandals!
Whoa!

03:26.717 --> 03:30.018
This is way better.
Come on, next one.

03:32.218 --> 03:34.258
Don't say "slow down," I'm begging you.
Hello?

03:34.258 --> 03:38.778
Kashu-san, here we go.
Ajiro-honte.

03:38.858 --> 03:40.138
Ajiro-honte.
Man, this is a pain.

03:40.798 --> 03:43.599
Writing all this down?
We'll need it.

03:43.599 --> 03:44.599
Hurry, hurry.
Uh...

03:44.859 --> 03:48.079
Keep going.
Shigure-chausu.

03:48.139 --> 03:50.119
Huh?
Ayagu.

03:50.159 --> 03:52.139
Shigure-chausu.
Shigure-chausu?

03:52.139 --> 03:54.300
No way, is that real?
Minamikawa-san, please be quiet.

03:54.700 --> 03:56.260
I can't hear.
Huh?

03:56.400 --> 03:58.940
This one, hata...
Hataori-chausu.

03:59.340 --> 04:02.000
Hataori-chausu.
Chance.

04:02.020 --> 04:03.240
There's no way that says "chance."
Huh?

04:04.086 --> 04:05.514
Chaushu.
Kashu-san, seriously?

04:05.821 --> 04:10.801
Weaving Chance?
No, I looked it up and this came up.

04:11.181 --> 04:14.661
Okay, list all 48 positions already.
Kashu-san, hurry, this is bad.

04:14.661 --> 04:15.421
I don't know. Huh?
Tsuru, tsuru... Tsuru-honte.

04:15.421 --> 04:21.422
Tsuru-honte.
Hahahaha.

04:22.162 --> 04:23.422
Kotobuki-honte.
Kotobuki-honte.

04:23.502 --> 04:27.082
Karakusai-chausu.
Karakusai-chausu.

04:28.683 --> 04:30.843
Karakusai-chausu?
That was fast.

04:31.183 --> 04:33.943
Oh no, oh no, oh no.
Hamachi... the fish plus bird.

04:33.943 --> 04:35.823
Hamachi?
Ah.

04:36.083 --> 04:38.383
Ugh.
Hey! What are you doing?

04:38.563 --> 04:41.644
Kashu-san seriously had no idea.
What the hell are you doing?

04:42.064 --> 04:44.104
He kept getting stuck on kanji he couldn't
read.

04:44.824 --> 04:51.225
It's gone, damn it. Takeda's still out
there. What do we do?

04:51.765 --> 04:55.685
Because of Kashu, I kept blurting stuff
out. It's over.

04:56.065 --> 04:59.785
Ugh.
This is impossible. It's endless.

05:00.805 --> 05:03.586
OK Google.
Tell me something fun.

05:04.086 --> 05:06.366
No progress at all.
Here's a riddle.

05:07.006 --> 05:11.706
A rotten egg and a graveyard at night.
What's the connection?

05:13.466 --> 05:14.727
They're both creepy.
Wow.

05:15.307 --> 05:19.747
Yeah.
That's not fun at all.

05:20.647 --> 05:23.307
That one was awful too.
You asked for it.

05:23.867 --> 05:28.508
Seriously, help us already.
A blender?

05:29.608 --> 05:30.608
A blender.
Oh!

05:30.608 --> 05:36.528
Blending candy won't help.
At least give us a drink.

05:36.989 --> 05:39.069
Let's set it aside for now.
So it'd be easier to eat?

05:39.069 --> 05:40.029
All right!
Huh?

05:40.029 --> 05:43.389
Hahahaha.
Cigarettes!

05:43.389 --> 05:45.449
Cigarettes.
Oh, wow.

05:45.669 --> 05:49.410
A smoke, huh.
Cigarettes really hit hard.

05:49.470 --> 05:51.130
Huh.

05:56.330 --> 05:59.310
That hits the spot.
It works.

06:01.091 --> 06:03.191
My eyes are wide open now.
That really hit.

06:05.091 --> 06:06.091
Whoa.
What happened?

06:06.091 --> 06:06.951
Did something come?
Ah, it did.

06:06.951 --> 06:07.951
Ah.
It came?

06:08.331 --> 06:09.971
It came.
Finally.

06:13.312 --> 06:15.372
Ah.
It's here.

06:16.592 --> 06:17.912
It's that woman.
Yu Aihara.

06:17.952 --> 06:19.972
Oh.
She's beautiful.

06:20.512 --> 06:22.673
Still beautiful.
Let's open the 48 positions.

06:22.933 --> 06:26.753
Let's go with Kanai-kun. Kanai-san, can I
leave the 48 positions to you?

06:26.993 --> 06:30.873
Oh, sure.
Hello?

06:30.873 --> 06:33.073
Hello, Kanai?
Sorry, got a second right now?

06:33.714 --> 06:37.074
You know the dirty 48 positions, right?
You know, positions?

06:37.514 --> 06:39.034
Oh, the 48 positions?
The 48 positions.

06:39.994 --> 06:46.315
Can you rattle them off to me in about ten
minutes? Ah, got it.

06:46.395 --> 06:48.435
I'll call you in about ten minutes.
Okay, got it.

06:48.435 --> 06:49.435
Sorry.
Yeah.

06:50.115 --> 06:54.515
By the time we finish the 48 positions,
the ramen'll be gone. / True.

06:54.515 --> 06:55.275
This might work.
Yeah.

06:55.275 --> 06:56.596
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

06:56.596 --> 06:58.836
Right, the 48 positions are
in a pretty important spot. / Yeah.

06:59.996 --> 07:03.216
Coffee!
Oh!

07:03.216 --> 07:07.136
Coffee with sweets is nice, right?
Bitter, bitter, bitter.

07:07.376 --> 07:10.297
Hahaha.
It's good.

07:10.897 --> 07:11.897
Good, huh?
Bitter, bitter.

07:11.977 --> 07:17.637
Mind if I get a sip? Just a drop.
That's what happens eating only sweets.

07:17.637 --> 07:21.298
Sure, sure.
Thanks.

07:25.110 --> 07:26.290
No thanks.
No thanks.

07:26.350 --> 07:29.990
Ah, coffee and cigarettes.
Ah. Huh? Oh!

07:29.990 --> 07:34.710
Ah.
It's a stove here.

07:34.910 --> 07:38.271
That startled me.
Want to grill a rice cracker?

07:38.971 --> 07:42.011
But at least it warms you up.
True.

07:42.271 --> 07:46.131
What do we use it for?
Wow, that's warm.

07:46.151 --> 07:47.591
Warm.
Nice and warm.

07:47.671 --> 07:48.751
Warm.
Ah.

07:49.211 --> 07:50.571
Use it for like ten seconds.
Yeah.

07:50.611 --> 07:53.591
Let's use it a bit.
A little more is fine.

07:55.111 --> 07:56.291
Warm.
Oh.

07:56.291 --> 07:56.871
Ah!
Yes!

07:56.871 --> 07:57.871
Yes!
Yes!

07:58.631 --> 08:02.171
This is really nice.
Ah.

08:02.411 --> 08:04.852
Ah.
It's not like we're full.

08:04.852 --> 08:08.032
True.
This might actually be good.

08:08.032 --> 08:09.072
Oh, it's pickled plum.
Yeah.

08:09.152 --> 08:12.472
This, this.
This.

08:12.712 --> 08:14.312
This.
This is it.

08:15.652 --> 08:19.392
If we can't get out, we'll be stuck
living like this... Ah! Ah!

08:20.152 --> 08:21.712
It's a stink bug.
Ugh.

08:21.852 --> 08:24.212
A damn stink bug.
Ugh, huge.

08:24.632 --> 08:26.332
Oh no.
I hate this.

08:28.032 --> 08:30.893
How did it even get in here?
Jeez.

08:31.073 --> 08:34.453
Why are there bugs in a sealed room?
Bugs can come and go freely.

08:34.453 --> 08:37.433
Exactly.
We haven't made any progress either.

08:37.433 --> 08:38.433
Hello?
Hello, you good?

08:39.593 --> 08:42.013
I'm good.
Okay, start rattling them off.

08:42.933 --> 08:43.933
Okay.
Go ahead, please.

08:44.033 --> 08:45.553
Okay.
Okay, here I go.

08:45.593 --> 08:47.953
Okay.
Ajiro-honte.

08:48.313 --> 08:49.893
Ajiro-honte.
Got it.

08:49.893 --> 08:51.593
Ajiro-honte.
Ageha-honte.

08:52.113 --> 08:55.074
Ageha-honte.
Ikada-honte.

08:55.754 --> 08:58.834
Ikada-honte.
Kotobuki-honte.

08:59.074 --> 09:00.654
Kotobuki-honte.
Kotobuki-honte.

09:01.654 --> 09:04.214
Horairi-honte.
Horairi-honte.

09:05.254 --> 09:08.314
Kasafune-honte.
Kasafune-honte.

09:09.374 --> 09:11.654
Sekirei-honte.
Sekirei-honte.

09:11.654 --> 09:13.414
Sekirei-honte?
Okay.

09:13.914 --> 09:15.554
Thanks.
Sekirei-honte.

09:15.554 --> 09:16.554
That helped.
Yeah.

09:16.834 --> 09:18.875
Hang in there.
Yeah.

09:18.935 --> 09:20.015
Oh, what a good junior.
Still 18 left.

09:21.255 --> 09:22.375
Yeah.
We used a lot, though.

09:22.375 --> 09:23.589
There are 48 of them.
Okay, let's go.

09:23.595 --> 09:27.075
Ah.
Name all 48 sex positions.

09:27.195 --> 09:28.315
Here we go.
Ajiro-honte.

09:29.235 --> 09:32.195
Ajiro-honte.
Ageho-honte.

09:33.075 --> 09:34.095
Okay.
Ikada-honte.

09:34.095 --> 09:35.815
Okay.
Kotobuki-honte.

09:45.576 --> 09:50.356
Okay.

09:51.936 --> 09:58.936
Futatsudomoe.

10:00.396 --> 10:01.956
Yeah.
Tachikanae.

10:02.556 --> 10:03.756
Yaguradachi.
Yeah.

10:04.476 --> 10:05.816
Sekirei-honte.
Okay.

10:05.956 --> 10:07.916
Yeah.
That's all 48 positions.

10:08.036 --> 10:09.837
How is it?
Hmm.

10:12.037 --> 10:13.037
Huh?
Did it work?

10:13.417 --> 10:15.677
Shouldn't that be okay?
Why not?

10:15.857 --> 10:17.017
Huh?
Huh?

10:17.957 --> 10:19.617
Oh no.
Something was wrong.

10:19.977 --> 10:21.657
No way.
Huh?

10:22.077 --> 10:24.677
No way.
Which one is wrong?

10:24.757 --> 10:28.297
Which one was wrong?
Huh?

10:28.297 --> 10:29.737
Huh?
This is bad.

10:30.837 --> 10:34.018
Why, though?
Oh man...

10:34.138 --> 10:36.278
Oh no.
This is a shock.

10:37.018 --> 10:41.238
This is like when a Dragon Quest revival
spell doesn't work. Total despair.

10:41.838 --> 10:45.178
With something this long,
even one wrong character...

10:45.178 --> 10:46.178
Exactly.
Ugh.

10:50.914 --> 10:53.154
A pot.
A stove.

10:54.894 --> 10:57.355
Maybe that's why it's here.
Ah, so with this...

10:58.295 --> 11:01.555
Ah.
How would that work?

11:01.555 --> 11:07.076
Like putting it on top later or something?
Why are mine always "later"?

11:07.076 --> 11:09.696
So many.
Nunokawa keeps hitting jackpots.

11:10.116 --> 11:12.756
Then that's huge.
Water.

11:14.556 --> 11:15.556
Water.
Water.

11:16.957 --> 11:18.957
Ah!
Water.

11:20.937 --> 11:22.357
Ah! Water.
Ah! Ah!

11:22.357 --> 11:23.357
Water.
Cold!

11:24.217 --> 11:26.577
Water.
All right.

11:28.758 --> 11:30.658
Damn it!
This sucks.

11:31.338 --> 11:34.398
If my partner turned into that...
What temperature is it now?

11:34.498 --> 11:36.178
Seven degrees.
It's dropping.

11:36.198 --> 11:39.139
It is dropping.
It is getting dark out.

11:39.139 --> 11:40.139
This is bad.
It's dropping.

11:40.379 --> 11:41.879
It's only going lower.
OK Google.

11:42.879 --> 11:49.160
Turn on the TV.
I'm sorry, I can't do that.

11:49.260 --> 11:50.620
It won't turn on?
Why not?

11:51.560 --> 11:56.200
Turn it on!
You can turn it on!

11:56.200 --> 11:57.843
OK Google.
Everyone's starting to lose it.

11:58.241 --> 12:01.981
You're totally useless.
I'm sorry.

12:02.781 --> 12:06.521
I hope I can evolve more
and be of better service to you.

12:07.381 --> 12:12.522
You're no help to me at all.
You won't even save us.

12:12.522 --> 12:16.022
We're all going crazy one by one.
You're useless. Drop dead!

12:16.022 --> 12:20.683
Whether toward me, a virtual assistant,
or toward anyone else,

12:20.803 --> 12:24.343
I hope people stop saying
things like that.

12:25.343 --> 12:29.704
What the hell?
It's giving me a lecture.

12:29.704 --> 12:33.824
Oh.
Hello, everyone.

12:33.824 --> 12:36.704
Hello, everyone. This is Skyrocket
Company. That's Yashiro there.

12:36.704 --> 12:40.745
I'm Mambou Yashiro.
Today again, from 5 to 8...

12:41.085 --> 12:43.485
we're live for three hours.
We can hear the radio.

12:43.525 --> 12:46.565
Here we go.
Today's topic is this.

12:48.505 --> 12:53.526
Life's little gambling moments.
What if Kessoku comes up too?

12:53.526 --> 12:55.946
"Life's Little Gambling Moments: The Time
I Took a Gamble!" Let's hear it.

12:55.946 --> 13:01.967
In your life so far, have you had a little
moment where it was all or nothing?

13:02.207 --> 13:06.667
All right then, let's get right into our
little gambling stories. / Hope it happens.

13:07.067 --> 13:11.868
Tokyo, 26-year-old construction worker,
"Imadoki." / Yes, Imadoki.

13:12.568 --> 13:16.508
My little gamble was when, in high school,
my girlfriend asked me...

13:17.208 --> 13:21.349
"Do you know what day it is today?"
Ahh.

13:21.449 --> 13:25.609
That's a gamble, all right.
Next, one from the email form.

13:25.609 --> 13:26.769
Oh.
A 44-year-old man.

13:27.629 --> 13:29.209
Oh, "Kido Ai-Raku"!
It's here! It's here!

13:29.209 --> 13:31.630
Kido Ai-Raku!
It's here! Kido Ai-Raku!

13:31.630 --> 13:38.010
Going out drinking with a boss
who always pays...

13:38.750 --> 13:40.871
and pretending to open your wallet at the
check, even though you don't even have 1,000 yen in it. This is great.

13:41.651 --> 13:44.271
Well, in a way...
that really is a kind of gamble.

13:44.531 --> 13:48.991
Since you didn't go withdraw any money.
Amazing!

13:48.991 --> 13:51.552
That's amazing.
That's amazing.

13:51.632 --> 13:54.492
That's amazing.
At 44...

13:55.212 --> 13:57.512
Kido Ai-Raku!
Kido Ai-Raku has...

13:57.512 --> 14:01.733
been acknowledged by the world.
He's losing it over this.

14:02.973 --> 14:08.753
Ahh, thank you.
Man, I'm so happy.

14:09.493 --> 14:12.954
I didn't know this could make me this
happy. I love Yashiro now.

14:14.334 --> 14:15.934
Amazing, amazing.
Wow.

14:16.134 --> 14:17.914
Yes!
This is huge, this is huge.

14:17.954 --> 14:21.354
Kido Ai-Raku made it.
So this is what it feels like.

14:21.934 --> 14:23.815
Hey.
Did you hear that?

14:23.875 --> 14:28.055
They said it.
Hey.

14:28.755 --> 14:33.576
...raku.
This is the last one, though.

14:34.716 --> 14:35.716
Michio.
Huh?

14:36.736 --> 14:38.356
This is the last one, right?
This really is the last one.

14:39.796 --> 14:44.617
Huh? We still haven't gotten any key hint
from this last one.

14:44.617 --> 14:45.937
Yeah.
Yeah.

14:46.017 --> 14:47.857
Yeah, nothing.
Right.

14:49.357 --> 14:50.497
Shoes.
Oh, shoes.

14:50.957 --> 14:52.978
Oh, shoes.
Oh, shoes.

14:53.178 --> 14:54.178
Shoes.
Oh!

14:55.058 --> 14:57.678
Those are better than sandals.

15:01.302 --> 15:03.242
Yeah, but still...
Hold on.

15:05.902 --> 15:10.143
There's no hint at all, really.
What if...

15:12.303 --> 15:14.863
The key hidden in the Candy House...
Yeah.

15:16.903 --> 15:20.124
is really somewhere in here?
That's what it means, right?

15:20.864 --> 15:22.764
Eat the wall.
We actually have to eat it?

15:23.064 --> 15:26.664
Huh? Like it's just hidden somewhere in
the wall?

15:26.724 --> 15:29.064
Man...
We have no choice but to eat it, do we?

15:29.224 --> 15:33.545
That's way too endless.
Maybe we don't have to eat it.

15:34.945 --> 15:38.405
Maybe there's another clue.
What came out?

15:38.405 --> 15:40.325
Ah!
It came in that fast?

15:40.365 --> 15:42.945
They're throwing it in.
From where?

15:45.336 --> 15:46.336
Jeez!
Zero affection.

15:46.846 --> 15:49.726
There? It was from up there, right?
That's scary.

15:50.786 --> 15:54.086
What if it had been iron or something?
Exactly.

15:54.406 --> 15:58.727
This is insane as it is. What if a pickaxe
came flying out of there?

15:59.207 --> 16:02.547
If it's a pickaxe, I'm killing you first.
That thing could stab anybody.

16:02.587 --> 16:04.527
Man, if it came down here...
It could stab anyone.

16:04.527 --> 16:08.348
Whoa!
Make peace, man. You're just too happy.

16:08.468 --> 16:11.268
Hold on, this is long.
Seriously, thank you.

16:11.268 --> 16:18.068
Oh, and it even came with this? So nice.
Iecchan.

16:18.068 --> 16:20.211
Go, go, go.
What do we do? Listen while we think?

16:20.269 --> 16:21.509
Yeah, listen while we work.
Listen while we work.

16:22.149 --> 16:23.209
This is the best.
You guys are close.

16:23.209 --> 16:25.089
I didn't know this could make me so happy.
Temporary ceasefire for now.

16:32.950 --> 16:35.850
Yeah.
He's a fugitive.

16:36.110 --> 16:38.330
A fugitive.
So this is his hideout, right?

16:42.991 --> 16:48.111
I'm about to cry.
I haven't even done anything good.

16:48.371 --> 16:50.651
True.
Man, this really is amazing.

16:52.151 --> 16:57.452
After all that trouble, we finally got it.
Maybe tomorrow will be brighter for us now.

16:58.432 --> 17:01.752
Even food tastes brighter now.
I want that too.

17:02.532 --> 17:03.612
Might make you fall in love.
Huh.

17:03.672 --> 17:06.552
First cigarette in a while.

17:10.163 --> 17:11.163
Take-chan?
Ah, hello?

17:11.353 --> 17:13.193
Ah, yeah.
Take-chan, ah, hello?

17:13.733 --> 17:15.953
How'd it go?
I just ate it.

17:15.953 --> 17:16.953
Oh!
You got it.

17:17.173 --> 17:20.934
Uh, I got a call from Minamikawa-san and
went to Kawasaki...

17:21.494 --> 17:26.154
I went to Karamenya Masumoto.
You actually went there first.

17:26.154 --> 17:27.174
Yeah, I just finished the bowl.
Yeah.

17:28.214 --> 17:32.235
And I figured out the words there, so I'd
like to tell Minamikawa-san. Go ahead.

17:32.955 --> 17:37.935
Okay. "Spicy, but delicious. Thank you for
finishing it."

17:37.935 --> 17:41.215
"Spicy, but delicious. Thank you for
finishing it," right? Yeah.

17:41.740 --> 17:42.811
Thanks.
Okay, bye.

17:43.636 --> 17:48.056
Yeah, sorry.
We're running low.

17:48.116 --> 17:50.016
All right.
Karamenya Masumoto.

17:51.716 --> 17:53.956
Ah, he really went.
Been a while.

17:54.517 --> 17:55.517
Oh.
Okay, okay.

17:55.517 --> 17:56.557
Quite a lot.
How about this?

17:57.637 --> 18:00.997
Ah, just a little more.
It opened up a lot.

18:02.537 --> 18:04.857
If the 48 positions open, that hole gets
huge, right? Yeah.

18:06.338 --> 18:11.658
Yeah. We still don't know which side is
top or bottom.

18:11.658 --> 18:13.318
Ah, no way.
Still impossible, huh?

18:13.438 --> 18:17.278
Seriously, those 48 positions...
Why won't that clue open?

18:17.398 --> 18:19.339
I think it's down to one character or
something. Yeah.

18:19.679 --> 18:24.779
That's the only thing that makes sense. I
think our part is right, mine and Minamikawa's.

18:25.219 --> 18:28.219
Yeah, that's what they said too.
It's Kanai-kun's reading.

18:29.039 --> 18:31.040
But we have no choice now.
We have to bet on the 48 positions.

18:32.020 --> 18:34.620
It's hard over the road noise.
Call Kanai one more time.

18:35.920 --> 18:38.760
That's scary.
Yeah, it is.

18:38.820 --> 18:42.681
It's just verification work now.
Can we do it with nine?

18:42.681 --> 18:43.321
Ah, hello?
Nine won't do it.

18:43.321 --> 18:45.921
Yeah, yeah.
Looks like the 48 positions are a bit off.

18:47.261 --> 18:50.501
What? Can you read them all again right
now? Or are you outside?

18:50.501 --> 18:54.842
Ah... ah, wait...
Hold on a sec. Maybe it's how we said it.

18:54.842 --> 18:57.562
Maybe it's how we said it. Sorry.
Ugh, it's ticking down.

18:57.662 --> 18:58.762
Ah, Kanai.
This is really bad.

18:58.842 --> 19:03.622
I'll call you right back.
I'm already outside.

19:03.622 --> 19:05.862
What do we do now?
Ugh.

19:08.602 --> 19:11.802
The 48 positions are all we have left.
That's it, just the 48 positions.

19:11.962 --> 19:15.083
This is all...
this.

19:16.343 --> 19:21.603
This, this, and this.
We should be able to take those off.

19:21.603 --> 19:23.823
That thing is right in the middle.
Perfectly placed.

19:28.233 --> 19:29.233
Oh, can you get through?

19:35.764 --> 19:42.164
I almost did.
Can I go out first?

19:42.504 --> 19:44.344
What?
You little...

19:45.664 --> 19:47.724
You think that's okay?
You think you can get out?

19:48.944 --> 19:52.504
No way, that's impossible.
We have to get out together.

19:54.144 --> 19:58.245
No, I don't think so. If one gets out,
what happens to the other one?

20:00.545 --> 20:03.485
How should I know? Figure that out
yourself. Hey!

20:04.605 --> 20:07.005
It gets way worse if there's only one of
us. Ugh.

20:07.025 --> 20:11.365
Whoa, this might actually work.
Whoa.

20:11.365 --> 20:15.785
Whoa, you can really do it.
Whoa, whoa.

20:15.825 --> 20:18.026
Ah, ah.
Yeah, of course that's what happens.

20:18.026 --> 20:19.026
Right.
Yeah.

20:20.666 --> 20:22.066
What the hell are you doing?
Your hand slipped off, right?

20:22.506 --> 20:23.806
Huh?
Your hand slipped off, didn't it?

20:25.766 --> 20:29.906
You can't get out, because I'm here.
No, wait. I can get out.

20:30.026 --> 20:32.006
No, no.
You can't get out.

20:32.666 --> 20:34.786
Practically speaking.
Because I'm here.

20:38.326 --> 20:42.007
Wait, let's at least guess.
Where the key might be.

20:43.107 --> 20:46.567
Maybe the baumkuchen?
But wait, the baumkuchen...

20:48.447 --> 20:50.607
It's unbelievably huge.
Ugh.

20:50.787 --> 20:54.847
The baumkuchen is high risk.
It's seriously high risk.

20:55.047 --> 20:57.467
This is rough.
This is really rough.

20:58.467 --> 21:01.768
Here we go.
Then smash it to bits.

21:01.768 --> 21:08.088
No, it won't. There's no moisture.
It'll just turn to powder.

21:08.088 --> 21:13.448
What is wrong with you?
Exactly.

21:13.828 --> 21:17.048
Let's just look inside the baumkuchen
first. True.

21:17.088 --> 21:19.308
Yeah.
We'll have to eat this later anyway.

21:19.688 --> 21:20.868
Right.
I'll eat it later.

21:20.868 --> 21:22.309
Yeah.
This.

21:22.369 --> 21:29.289
Ugh.
It's stacked like spare toilet paper.

21:29.509 --> 21:33.109
I see.
It really is how you store toilet paper.

21:33.169 --> 21:36.289
I see.
Huh?

21:37.689 --> 21:42.309
No, see, I knew it.
That's what it is.

21:42.309 --> 21:44.770
Hm?
No, I just mean...

21:47.050 --> 21:51.130
Like maybe it's inside the wheat-gluten
snack. I don't even know what that means.

21:51.450 --> 21:53.650
Then we just have to keep eating.
Yeah, maybe it's buried inside.

21:53.810 --> 21:56.710
I don't want to accept that reality.
Oh, that's what you meant.

21:56.710 --> 21:59.890
I don't want to think anymore.
Let's save this for later.

22:00.030 --> 22:01.550
Then we're counting on you.
Yeah, okay, okay.

22:01.550 --> 22:06.791
Okay.
But there wasn't a key inside, so...

22:08.891 --> 22:12.411
I don't get why we have to eat it.
No, because we already took it out.

22:13.031 --> 22:18.931
It's the rule.
We have to see it through.

22:19.931 --> 22:20.951
Ah, hello?
Hello?

22:20.951 --> 22:22.051
Hello.
Can you say them?

22:22.091 --> 22:24.351
I can, I can.
You can? Then maybe we can do this.

22:24.644 --> 22:26.359
Say it, say it, say it.
Fast is fine.

22:26.572 --> 22:30.292
Okay, hang on, I'll put Shinichi on.
Just rattle them off to him.

22:30.292 --> 22:31.292
Yeah.
Yeah.

22:31.626 --> 22:32.912
Okay, Kanai-kun, here we go.
Here I go.

22:32.912 --> 22:35.792
Okay.
Here I go. Are you ready?

22:35.972 --> 22:37.852
Okay, go ahead.
Tachikanae.

22:38.592 --> 22:40.772
Huh? You're starting there?
Not "Aji no Honte"?

22:40.872 --> 22:44.152
Uh, well, it depends on the site.
Oh no.

22:44.152 --> 22:45.366
Oh, I see.
The sets are kind of different.

22:46.092 --> 22:47.693
"Tachikanae."
This is going to take a while.

22:47.833 --> 22:53.753
"Tachikanae" is on here. Okay, okay.
I think this one's probably accurate.

22:53.813 --> 22:57.473
This list has all 48,
so I'll just read them off.

22:57.553 --> 22:58.753
I see.
Okay.

22:58.753 --> 22:59.833
"Chidori no Kyoku."
Why?

23:00.833 --> 23:01.833
"Chidori no Kyoku."
"Chidori song"?

23:01.913 --> 23:05.453
That's completely different. I've never
heard of "Chidori no Kyoku" in my life.

23:05.613 --> 23:07.573
Man, that's scary.
What the hell?

23:07.673 --> 23:12.214
That 48 positions list from before
was just Wikipedia.

23:12.234 --> 23:15.174
I checked a few sites,
and this 48-item version came up most.

23:15.914 --> 23:17.054
That one.
That's the right one.

23:17.194 --> 23:19.894
So that's the real one.
Probably the accurate version...

23:19.954 --> 23:23.554
Then everything from before was wrong.
We should just restart from the top.

23:23.934 --> 23:28.790
Then tell us.
"Tachikanae," okay, go on.

23:29.210 --> 23:33.330
Please.
Sorry, uh, "Chidori no Kyoku."

23:33.330 --> 23:34.510
"Chidori no Kyoku."
Oh no.

23:34.510 --> 23:37.911
Oh no, you idiot.
I told you that already.

23:39.151 --> 23:43.231
Kanai suddenly blurted out
"Chidori no Kyoku," of all things.

23:43.771 --> 23:45.551
That was the first I'd heard it.
First time I'd ever heard it.

23:46.111 --> 23:49.211
What did he say?
"Chidori no Kyoku"?

23:49.211 --> 23:52.071
I was like, "Chidori no Kyoku?"
That definitely wasn't on there.

23:53.031 --> 23:58.252
How many are there?
See, the earlier one was from Wikipedia.

23:58.252 --> 24:01.272
I knew it.
And the one I just found...

24:01.932 --> 24:03.732
is probably the official one.
Right?

24:04.292 --> 24:07.472
So how many are different?
I don't know that either.

24:07.492 --> 24:08.752
You don't know?
So we have to start from one.

24:09.372 --> 24:13.473
There are some matches, but
we have to hear them from the top.

24:13.533 --> 24:20.333
We don't know which ones are wrong.
How long is this radio show on till?

24:20.333 --> 24:21.333
It's three hours.
Three hours, till eight.

24:21.333 --> 24:24.953
We don't even know how many answers there
are, so let's just send in a ton of them.

24:25.433 --> 24:29.933
Let's just go with pickaxe first.
It is a pickaxe, right?

24:30.073 --> 24:32.514
Then how about "Tsuruhashi Hideki"?
"Tsuruhashi Hideki."

24:32.654 --> 24:37.394
Lead with "Tsuruhashi Hideki."
Like when you tap your Suica, you know?

24:39.074 --> 24:40.994
That one.
It's on right now.

24:41.294 --> 24:43.954
Like, you don't know if there's money on
it, but you tap it anyway.

24:43.994 --> 24:48.655
I kind of remember it. I remember
thinking, "Uh-oh, next one's bad."

24:49.155 --> 24:51.535
Isn't that perfect?
It's a relatable topic.

24:51.535 --> 24:57.535
That's really good. I like clams, but I
hate clams with sand in them.

24:58.135 --> 25:03.095
At an izakaya, when I eat steamed clams, I
put them in my mouth praying there's no sand.

25:03.935 --> 25:07.996
When there's no sand, it feels like I won,
and it tastes twice as good.

25:09.716 --> 25:12.396
No, that's the one.
Takano.

25:13.696 --> 25:16.056
He might be a natural.
Let's go with that.

25:16.056 --> 25:20.356
I don't know.
It doesn't feel that relatable.

25:22.096 --> 25:26.077
This is getting me down.
We're just stuck here, buried.

25:26.077 --> 25:28.557
It's getting dark out.
Yeah.

25:28.757 --> 25:31.137
It's getting dark and it's starting to
rain. It really is raining.

25:31.337 --> 25:33.677
Now it's raining too.
Turn on the lights.

25:35.877 --> 25:37.097
Oh!
Hah!

25:37.917 --> 25:39.877
The lights came on.
Oh, thank God.

25:39.957 --> 25:44.998
It's bright now.
The dark was freaking you out.

25:45.058 --> 25:46.258
Thank God.
Thank God.

25:48.678 --> 25:52.418
Okay, Google. Thanks.
You're very welcome.

25:52.758 --> 25:54.878
You're thanking it already.
At this point...

25:56.138 --> 25:58.958
In this situation.
All it did was turn on the light.

25:59.178 --> 26:02.579
It was getting dark,
and you're thanking it.

26:03.859 --> 26:10.619
Hey, Shinichi.
Play a song.

26:12.749 --> 26:19.749
My heart's getting worn down.

26:21.860 --> 26:27.240
Whoa.
Wh-wh-why is that?

26:29.400 --> 26:36.321
Why doesn't kombu make broth in the ocean?
Why is that?

26:36.421 --> 26:40.821
Why is that? Why is that?
Tetsu and Tom.

26:40.821 --> 26:42.781
Wh-wh-why, this is so sad.
Why, why?

26:43.221 --> 26:44.681
Why is that?
Why, why is that?

26:44.701 --> 26:46.561
Why is that?
Why, why?

26:46.721 --> 26:49.841
Why, why?
Why, why is that?

27:00.514 --> 27:03.574
Man, I just want to go home.
This one really hits.

27:03.628 --> 27:04.700
Why, though?
I've never felt like this before.

27:05.194 --> 27:10.895
That's not cigarette smoke.
It's so cold our breath is white.

27:10.895 --> 27:12.455
Whoa, yeah.
It's freezing now.

27:12.955 --> 27:15.675
Like that.
No, it really is cold.

27:15.775 --> 27:20.455
Should we mix in one heater request?
A heater.

27:20.775 --> 27:26.596
Maybe not a heater, but a blanket.
A blanket would be nice.

27:26.976 --> 27:28.196
We need a blanket.
Yeah, we do.

27:29.076 --> 27:31.616
Did you put the rice crackers in?
Start with the kakino-tane.

27:33.276 --> 27:35.757
Add a little water.
Oh, we're cooking now.

27:36.166 --> 27:37.737
This makes it spicy first.
Just changes the flavor a little.

27:37.737 --> 27:44.037
I see, I see.
Then add a bunch of marshmallows.

27:44.037 --> 27:45.937
We've got plenty of ingredients.
Whoa.

27:47.017 --> 27:48.998
Huh?
So it's an arranged recipe.

27:49.238 --> 27:52.558
Could chocolate be part of it?
Yeah, maybe.

27:53.938 --> 27:57.018
All right.
Won't that make it harder to eat?

27:57.538 --> 27:59.098
I wonder if this'll work.
Yeah.

27:59.098 --> 28:04.019
Smell-wise, it's not bad.

28:04.079 --> 28:08.659
I'm only going by the smell.
Right?

28:08.819 --> 28:10.499
Oh, it melts more than I expected.
Yeah.

28:10.499 --> 28:13.219
It's getting all soggy now.

28:13.219 --> 28:14.219
Yeah.

28:15.649 --> 28:22.649
You're a pro.

28:24.180 --> 28:25.280
It's good.
Really?

28:25.660 --> 28:27.260
Huh.
Oh, it's spicy.

28:27.700 --> 28:30.341
So it is spicy.
Oh, sweet and spicy.

28:30.421 --> 28:32.021
Sweet and spicy.
You haven't even tried it.

28:32.161 --> 28:33.161
You could just set it down.
Is it fate?

28:34.301 --> 28:36.461
Soy-sauce cracker.
You haven't even eaten it.

28:37.601 --> 28:41.061
Actually, adding the cracker might work.
What are you doing?

28:43.061 --> 28:48.002
Whoa, it's here!
Come over here.

28:48.062 --> 28:49.982
He's here.
Kanai-kun.

28:51.662 --> 28:54.622
Ah, hello?
Kanai-kun, can you do it now?

28:54.662 --> 29:00.023
Yeah, I'm good.
Can you do that new 48-positions list?

29:00.103 --> 29:03.283
Okay.
Right, uh, "Tachikanae."

29:03.703 --> 29:05.623
"Tachikanae."
That was on the earlier list too.

29:05.803 --> 29:07.063
Okay.
"Tachikanae," got it.

29:07.883 --> 29:10.643
Okay, uh, "Chidori no Kyoku."
"Chidori no Kyoku."

29:10.683 --> 29:13.204
"Chidori no Kyoku."
Okay.

29:13.304 --> 29:17.104
"Tachi Matsuba."
"Tachi Matsuba."

29:17.744 --> 29:18.944
That one wasn't on there.
Okay.

29:19.944 --> 29:21.504
"Miyama."
"Miyama."

29:21.564 --> 29:25.264
"Miyama" wasn't there either.
"Hiyodorigoe no..."

29:25.565 --> 29:30.745
"Hiyodorigoe no Sakao-toshi."
"Sakao-toshi."

29:30.765 --> 29:36.325
"Hiyodorigoe no Sakao-toshi."
"Kubihiki Renbo."

29:36.325 --> 29:37.785
Whoa.
"Kubihiki Renbo"?

29:39.085 --> 29:42.686
I can't make it out.
"Kubihiki Renbo."

29:42.826 --> 29:44.406
"Kubihiki Renbo."
Okay.

29:44.686 --> 29:46.706
"...renbo."
So it's with a B, right?

29:46.706 --> 29:47.706
With a B, right?
It's "bo."

29:47.706 --> 29:50.566
And last is "Tsubame-gaeshi."
"Tsubame-gaeshi."

29:51.296 --> 29:52.296
Okay.
That's all.

29:52.426 --> 29:54.027
Thanks, I'm hanging up.
Okay.

29:54.167 --> 29:55.167
Oh.
That's the end.

29:55.167 --> 29:59.827
Wait a second.
He flew through that.

29:59.827 --> 30:01.647
One, two, three...
Totally different.

30:01.647 --> 30:02.447
1, 2, 3... 48.

30:02.447 --> 30:03.447
It's all 48.

30:06.567 --> 30:09.068
It's there.
Here we go.

30:10.268 --> 30:12.968
All 48 positions.
Please.

30:12.968 --> 30:14.748
Here we go.
"Chidori no Kyoku."

30:15.208 --> 30:16.528
Okay.
"Tachikanae."

30:16.828 --> 30:18.048
Got it.
"Tachi Matsuba."

30:18.868 --> 30:20.609
"Miyama."
"Tachi Hanabishi."

30:20.609 --> 30:23.729
Got it.
"Hiyodorigoe no Sakao-toshi."

30:23.889 --> 30:25.429
Right.
"Koban-zeme."

30:25.809 --> 30:28.209
Okay.
Ah, sorry.

30:28.349 --> 30:29.689
"Goban-zeme."
"Goban-zeme."

30:29.689 --> 30:31.569
I didn't hear that one.
"Kubihiki Renbo."

30:32.109 --> 30:35.050
"Daki Jizo."
"Daruma-gaeshi."

30:35.190 --> 30:36.710
Okay.
"Midare Botan."

30:37.690 --> 30:40.310
"Butsudan-gaeshi."
"Kiku Ichimonji."

30:40.960 --> 30:41.960
"Matsuba-kuzushi."
"Tsubame-gaeshi."

30:42.270 --> 30:44.350
No, no, no.
Whoa.

30:46.730 --> 30:48.491
What?
Please.

30:48.491 --> 30:51.751
This is brutal.
Whoa.

30:52.271 --> 30:54.251
Whoa.
Huh?

30:55.751 --> 30:57.011
This is a shock.
Huh?

30:59.911 --> 31:02.112
Huh?
Which one?

31:03.872 --> 31:07.912
Come on, what the hell?
What's the problem?

31:07.912 --> 31:10.452
Because we don't know which one's wrong.
What do you mean, what?

31:11.592 --> 31:15.733
Now then, today's small gamble in life.
Here it is, here it is!

31:15.733 --> 31:16.993
"That was when I took a gamble!"
Seriously?

31:16.993 --> 31:18.973
We got this through the mail form.
Oh.

31:19.253 --> 31:24.013
Forty-three-year-old Tsuruhashi Hideki.
Oh!

31:24.933 --> 31:27.373
Tsuruhashi Hideki.
Amazing.

31:27.433 --> 31:30.214
So he likes clams.
Clams are good.

31:31.274 --> 31:34.034
But he hates clams with sand in them.
You're a genius.

31:34.034 --> 31:35.174
He's a genius.
This guy's hilarious.

31:35.174 --> 31:39.494
He's hilarious, a genius.
Okay, Google.

31:41.554 --> 31:44.934
This is rough, help me.
This is just getting depressing.

31:46.734 --> 31:49.975
All we can do is get really gloomy.
This is rough, help me.

31:50.675 --> 31:54.555
You've been working hard every day.
You must be exhausted.

31:55.375 --> 32:00.435
Don't forget to take a break.
If we stop like this, we're dead.

32:03.055 --> 32:07.515
Okay, Google.
Give me some words of encouragement.

32:07.535 --> 32:11.576
Whoa.
Think back on the road you've taken so far.

32:12.376 --> 32:16.936
If you've made it this far,
you should still be able to keep moving forward.

32:16.956 --> 32:20.096
Mm-hmm.
So we literally can't move.

32:20.096 --> 32:21.956
Because we're buried here.
We're not buried.

32:21.956 --> 32:24.876
Nice words, though.
Okay, Google.

32:24.876 --> 32:28.996
I can't move forward.
It's giving you good advice.

32:29.896 --> 32:30.897
Sorry, I couldn't understand that.
That's what you said.

32:36.257 --> 32:37.257
A jab.
Oh!

32:37.257 --> 32:40.477
Today's wild, really wild.
They keep coming.

32:40.477 --> 32:42.177
They're coming nonstop.
Whoa.

32:42.217 --> 32:43.577
Wait, what's this?
Hey.

32:45.197 --> 32:47.157
It's a person?
That's dangerous.

32:47.977 --> 32:51.598
Of course it is.
It really is from over there.

32:51.638 --> 32:57.258
Hello?
I'm going to read them now.

32:57.998 --> 33:01.158
Right, we need to read them from our side.
I'll read them, can you check?

33:01.158 --> 33:04.918
Can I use the same order as before? Yeah,
I'll just run through them in that order.

33:05.278 --> 33:06.658
Okay.
"Chidori no Kyoku."

33:08.078 --> 33:11.438
"Hiyodorigoe no Sakao-toshi."
It's sakao-toshi, right?

33:11.899 --> 33:13.419
Huh, "sakao"?
Damn, this is where it went wrong.

33:14.248 --> 33:15.390
Yes, the "sakao" in sakao-toshi.
So it was sakao-toshi.

33:15.759 --> 33:16.759
Okay.
Okay.

33:16.999 --> 33:18.679
Okay, okay, okay.
Okay.

33:18.839 --> 33:21.679
Then "Goban-zeme."
"Goban-zeme."

33:21.899 --> 33:25.519
"Kubihiki Renbo."
"Kubihiki Renbo."

33:26.319 --> 33:27.499
Okay.
Wait, Kubihiki?

33:28.559 --> 33:33.920
Ah. It's kubi-hiki,
then renbo ending in "bo."

33:33.920 --> 33:38.360
Right, Kubihiki Renbo.
I kept hearing just "hiki" the whole time.

33:38.360 --> 33:39.360
"Tsubame-gaeshi."
"Tsubame-gaeshi."

33:40.121 --> 33:41.479
Okay.
Thanks, sorry, thank you.

33:41.479 --> 33:42.479
No problem.
Okay.

33:44.780 --> 33:47.040
Damn it.
Here we go, here we go.

33:47.100 --> 33:50.180
All right.
Wait, hold on, Ukihashi and...

33:51.260 --> 33:52.960
Uh, let me try that again.
"Chidori no Kyoku."

33:53.761 --> 33:55.741
"Tachikanae."
"Tachi Matsuba."

33:56.421 --> 33:58.541
"Miyama."
"Tachi Hanabishi."

33:59.721 --> 34:01.761
"Hiyodorigoe no Sakao-toshi."
Right.

34:02.741 --> 34:04.581
"Goban-zeme."
Here.

34:04.581 --> 34:07.161
"Kubihiki Renbo."
"Shibori Fuyo."

34:07.261 --> 34:09.781
"Naruto."
"Kiku Ichimonji."

34:09.781 --> 34:11.181
"Matsuba-kuzushi."
"Tsubame-gaeshi."

34:11.341 --> 34:15.942
Please. Please.
Whoa. Whoa.

34:15.942 --> 34:21.762
Whoa.

34:25.062 --> 34:28.042
This is hopeless.
It's hard.

34:28.122 --> 34:31.542
No, this should work.
Seriously, this has to be it.

34:31.602 --> 34:35.483
Let's seriously go with this.
This has a real shot.

34:35.483 --> 34:38.003
I've never seen an escape like this.
What do we do?

34:38.083 --> 34:39.463
What do we do?
Go.

34:40.403 --> 34:42.963
Wait, damn it.
Try scraping it a little.

34:44.443 --> 34:50.743
Wait, wait, hold on.
Push harder.

34:50.743 --> 34:52.843
Go, go.
Man, my hand slipped.

34:53.403 --> 34:56.724
No way.
So that's how it works?

34:56.724 --> 34:59.384
Ah!
We did scratch it.

34:59.504 --> 35:02.724
But...
This is where it starts.

35:03.004 --> 35:08.784
Let's go from this side.
Oh!

35:11.024 --> 35:17.125
Wait, we might be able to do it.
No, this is impossible for amateurs.

35:18.165 --> 35:20.445
Open!
Are you kidding me?

35:22.265 --> 35:24.445
Whoa.
Go, it feels like it might work.

35:26.425 --> 35:30.485
What is this material?
Halfway through it totally changes.

35:30.485 --> 35:31.485
Ow.
Whoa.

35:32.145 --> 35:35.565
What is this made of?
Wait.

35:35.565 --> 35:38.666
Let me try once.
Wait, that much?

35:39.206 --> 35:43.366
Just watch your hands.
They go numb fast. Ah!

35:43.366 --> 35:45.326
Not even close.
Maybe this is impossible.

36:01.986 --> 36:05.306
They probably meant it to be Ukihashi.
Wait, what? Is it painted white?

36:07.006 --> 36:09.386
Something's off.
This is no good.

36:09.786 --> 36:12.707
This material makes it impossible.
I can't even tell what it is.

36:13.547 --> 36:17.387
Careful, careful, careful.
There, there, there!

36:18.187 --> 36:19.187
Ah.
Ah, ah.

36:19.447 --> 36:21.767
What?
Wait, wait, this...

36:22.267 --> 36:23.547
This is the worst, probably.
Huh?

36:23.887 --> 36:25.327
This is insane.
Ah.

36:26.567 --> 36:27.567
This is insane.
It's metal, metal.

36:27.627 --> 36:29.507
It's metal, right? Metal.
There's metal inside.

36:30.547 --> 36:33.127
You've got to be kidding me.
It's metal.

36:33.328 --> 36:37.588
No, it's definitely metal.
Whoa.

36:37.888 --> 36:44.668
Let's stop.
Whoa, it comes this far?

36:44.668 --> 36:49.488
I have no idea.
If it's all metal, no wonder it's cold.

36:50.288 --> 36:51.888
That's why it's freezing cold.
Yeah.

36:52.268 --> 36:54.329
Whoa.
Wait a second, something's...

36:56.389 --> 36:58.449
A ton of bugs are gathering.
Whoa.

36:59.289 --> 37:00.989
Because of the light.
We've got the light on.

37:01.609 --> 37:03.449
Hey.
I hate bugs. They scare me.

37:03.449 --> 37:06.549
Okay, Google.
Turn off the light.

37:06.909 --> 37:08.189
What's "okay" about this?
Okay, Google.

37:08.189 --> 37:11.029
Okay, Siri.
Whoa, it turned off.

37:11.429 --> 37:12.429
Ah.
What?

37:12.609 --> 37:14.289
Scary, scary, scary.
Whoa.

37:14.289 --> 37:16.370
Whoa, it's intense.
Whoa.

37:16.370 --> 37:18.430
Whoa.
What?

37:18.430 --> 37:19.190
Huh?
What?

37:19.190 --> 37:20.170
Scary.
Whoa.

37:20.170 --> 37:23.610
Whoa.
What is it?

37:26.580 --> 37:27.580
What do we do?
What is it?

37:27.930 --> 37:32.050
Maybe bugs don't come to this side as
much. Ugh.

37:32.050 --> 37:33.121
What now?
Okay, Google.

37:35.790 --> 37:37.991
Turn the light on.
I'm scared.

37:37.991 --> 37:40.411
Yeah, that's scary.
I really hate this.

37:41.231 --> 37:44.731
Forget the bugs.
No light is scarier.

37:44.731 --> 37:46.651
True.
Was that a blackout?

37:46.951 --> 37:51.011
No, not a blackout here.
Oh.

37:51.091 --> 37:55.291
What?
It freaks you out.

37:55.291 --> 37:56.171
Whoa, scary, scary.
What is it?

37:56.171 --> 37:57.552
Uh, uh, uh...
Oh, it's back on.

37:59.352 --> 38:00.352
Ah.
What? What is it?

38:01.332 --> 38:02.652
This is terrifying.
What?

38:03.192 --> 38:05.152
What, what?
Did the breaker trip?

38:05.152 --> 38:08.752
What does that mean?
What?

38:11.012 --> 38:15.772
Was it a mistake?
Or did it mean something?

38:16.292 --> 38:20.533
A hint?
Or it could send us the wrong way.

38:21.273 --> 38:26.153
Let's take it as a hint.
Did it go dark because we said that?

38:26.153 --> 38:27.673
Huh?
What did you say?

38:28.893 --> 38:32.613
You mean it's linked to Kuro-chan's sound?
No... but it did feel that way.

38:32.633 --> 38:38.994
Heave-ho.
If we add the foothold too...

38:38.994 --> 38:44.954
True.
Huh?

38:48.034 --> 38:49.134
Huh?
Oh.

38:49.574 --> 38:50.574
Huh?
Huh?

38:50.574 --> 38:52.794
I think this is it, this is it.
Wait, wait, wait!

38:52.794 --> 38:54.574
Huh? Huh?
That looks like a key.

38:55.914 --> 39:00.975
Oh, it's here, it's here!
It's here!

39:02.841 --> 39:04.555
Look.
Look, look!

39:04.555 --> 39:05.555
No way.
Wait.

39:05.555 --> 39:07.155
Whoa.
How did you even find that?

39:07.475 --> 39:09.575
That's definitely a key.
It has to be.

39:09.595 --> 39:11.355
It's not a 500-yen coin or something,
right? Here I go.

39:11.675 --> 39:16.775
Wait, can you see it?
Yeah, I can. Okay.

39:16.775 --> 39:17.475
It's a key.
Oh!

39:17.475 --> 39:19.795
There it is!
Yes!

39:20.055 --> 39:23.636
Yes! We did it!
This is intense.

39:23.926 --> 39:24.926
All right.
We've been waiting for this.

39:26.216 --> 39:29.876
All right.
Yes, yes, yes!

39:29.956 --> 39:32.236
First, this one.
Question is whether it fits.

39:32.496 --> 39:33.516
Hey, you're quick.

39:37.936 --> 39:39.776
Oh, yes.
We did it!

39:39.816 --> 39:41.697
We did it!
We did it!

39:42.237 --> 39:43.897
This nearly killed us.
All right.

39:44.237 --> 39:49.917
Yes!
Yes!

39:49.937 --> 39:51.397
All right.
I'm seriously so happy.

39:51.777 --> 39:53.157
I'm seriously so happy.
How does this even work?

39:55.517 --> 39:57.457
This is it, it is!
Huh?

39:58.597 --> 40:03.678
We can get outside! We can get outside!
This feels amazing.

40:03.678 --> 40:04.678
Let's go.
Here I go.

40:05.158 --> 40:08.642
Come on.
I'm out!

40:09.722 --> 40:12.282
We did it! We did it!
Yes! All right!

40:12.282 --> 40:14.622
All right!
We really did it!

40:14.622 --> 40:15.542
We're outside! We did it!
Oh! Oh!

40:15.542 --> 40:20.083
All right.
Amazing.

40:20.143 --> 40:21.783
All right.
Oh, we got out.

40:21.843 --> 40:23.103
All right.
All right.

40:23.243 --> 40:26.863
We did it!
We did it!

40:26.863 --> 40:30.043
Yeah! Yeah! All right!
Man, that feels good.

40:30.073 --> 40:31.073
It's cold out.
Seriously.

40:34.563 --> 40:35.863
Wait, where are we?
Yeah, good point.

40:36.593 --> 40:37.593
Oh.
I see.

40:37.923 --> 40:41.363
So it ends here.
Only Tom Brown escaped?

40:41.383 --> 40:43.283
Oh, wow.
Amazing.

40:43.283 --> 40:44.484
That's amazing.
Though...

40:45.324 --> 40:46.964
They were at their limit.
Yeah.

40:47.224 --> 40:49.184
Man.
My stomach too.

40:49.304 --> 40:50.644
Yeah.
That was close.

40:50.644 --> 40:53.204
Mentally too.
One by one,

40:54.344 --> 40:56.784
you start to lose it.
Everybody gradually loses it.

40:57.424 --> 40:59.864
That 48-positions one in Minamikawa's
room. That one.

41:00.244 --> 41:03.764
That puzzle was really well designed.
Yeah, really well designed.

41:03.784 --> 41:06.965
It's built expecting
all of that to happen.

41:07.105 --> 41:10.625
We know where the mistake was,
but they didn't.

41:11.045 --> 41:15.345
They didn't know what was wrong,
or how many things were wrong.

41:15.825 --> 41:19.405
For all they knew, all of it could've been
wrong. That was brutal.

41:19.405 --> 41:23.185
Amazing.
Kuro-chan made zero progress.

41:23.205 --> 41:25.145
Yeah.
Nothing changed at all.

41:25.445 --> 41:29.005
It's incredible, though.
Even with no progress, it still holds up.

41:29.045 --> 41:31.926
Seriously. Normally you'd never see
something like this.

41:32.306 --> 41:33.546
It just got dark.
Yeah.

41:34.306 --> 41:35.646
Yeah, exactly.
That guy...

41:37.606 --> 41:41.026
Has he ever done a harder job
than this in his life?

41:41.046 --> 41:46.386
Probably not.
This might be his absolute limit.

41:46.386 --> 41:47.386
Probably.
Probably.

41:47.606 --> 41:49.986
He's done all kinds of stuff,
but this might be the roughest one yet.

41:50.346 --> 41:53.046
I think this is max difficulty.
You can't even move.

41:53.507 --> 41:54.867
And nobody's there.
Yeah.

41:55.627 --> 41:58.367
And that other room...
What do you make of that?

41:58.727 --> 42:00.707
Right.
It's such a brute-force setup.

42:00.707 --> 42:01.767
Exactly.
Exactly.

42:02.187 --> 42:04.907
It's basically,
throw him in a room and trap him.

42:04.977 --> 42:06.977
You just think, "Smash it open."
Yeah, exactly, exactly.

42:06.987 --> 42:11.827
So naturally you think, "Use the pickaxe."
You don't usually see that in an escape show.

42:15.187 --> 42:18.268
Let's smash it with the pickaxe.
But is that even the right move?

42:18.268 --> 42:19.968
But we don't know either.
We don't know the answer.
